# MUI Component Patterns

## Theme Setup

- Use `createTheme()` with `palette.mode: 'dark'` and custom M3-aligned overrides
- Background: super dark gray (`#0A0A0F`–`#111118`), surfaces progressively lighter for elevation
- No shadows on dark backgrounds (they disappear) — use 1px borders in neutral accent + lighter surface grays for elevation

## Component Styling

### Cards & Panels
- 1px neutral accent border, rounded 8px
- Surface elevation via progressively lighter grays
- Hover: elevation lift + primary border glow (150ms)

### Buttons
- Primary: filled with primary accent, white text, hover glow (box-shadow with accent at low opacity)
- Secondary: outlined primary border, accent text
- Destructive: filled error accent, white text

### Inputs & Badges
- Rounded corners: 4px for inputs/badges, 8px for cards
- Status badges: filled, rounded, accent background at ~20% with full-color text
- Active edit cell: primary border at full opacity with inner glow

### MUI X Data Grid (N6)
- Row hover: primary wash 8% + faint primary left border (150ms)
- Selected rows: primary wash 15% + solid primary left border
- No alternating row striping — hover provides contrast
- Column headers: neutral background (slightly lighter than surface), bold white text
- Row dividers: neutral at 15% opacity
- Collapsible groups: suite accent color 4px left border on header row
- Multi-select: checkbox with primary accent, ripple 150ms

### Filter Bar
- Chips above grid in horizontal bar
- Active filter: filled with semantic color of filtered value (e.g., Pass → Success chip)
- Inactive filter: neutral outlined chip

### Toasts (Snackbar)
- Slide in from top-right, 300ms in / 200ms out
- Left border + icon colored by semantic type (success/error/warning/info)
- Frosted glass effect: `backdrop-filter: blur()` + dark translucent background on tooltips

### Charts (N5)
- Full accent palette for chart segments
- Dark grid lines: neutral at 30%
- Tooltip: frosted glass
- Bars animate in sequentially (50ms stagger)
